A student shall be considered to have completed a course successfully and earned the credits if he/she secures an acceptable letter grade in the range A+ to E as given below. Letter grade ‘F’ in any course implies failure of the student in that course and no credits earned. Absent is also treated as no credits earned.

Computation of SGPA and CGPA

The UGC recommends the following procedure to compute the Semester Grade Point Average (SGPA) and Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA):

SGPA:

It is the ratio of sum of the product of the number of credits with the grade points scored by a student in all the courses taken by a student and the sum of the total number of credits of all the courses undergone/registered by a student, i.e.,

SGPA= {sum of (grade * credits) in every subject}/sum of credits for all subjects

CGPA:

The CGPA is calculated in the same manner taking into account all the courses/subjects registered by student over all the semesters of a Programme i.e., in all eight semesters
CGPA= {sum of (sgpa in that sem * credits earned in that sem) }/sum of credits in all semesters

PERCENTAGE:

Percentage = (CGPA – 0.75) x 10
